@node Distribution

QAmiTrack and its source code are in the public domain.
Do whatever you like with them... although if you're nice
you'll give me a credit in your docs.  ;)

@endnode

@node KnownProblems

None!  (really this time ;))
  
@endnode

@node History

1.92 : (Public Release 2/20/98)
 - Added detectlogon.rexx to the standard distribution.
   detectlogon.rexx is a way to have QAmiTrack notify
   you when certain people come on line.  See the beginning
   of detectlogon.rexx for details.
 - Launched programs now inherit QAmiTrack's stack size,
   rather than always having 4096 bytes of stack.
 - Added "Beep on Log Entry" item to the Options menu,
   to the startup arguments, and to the ARexx get/set commands.
 * Fixed a bug in the Connect program launching code that
   was causing occasional system crashes.  (I had forgot
   to include a TAG_END in my SystemTags() call, so it was
   reading random arguments off the stack!)

1.91 : (Public Release 1/22/98)
 - QAmiTrack now displays its window coordinates in the
   title bar after a resize operation.
 - Added a "Reset Comment" item to the Options menu.
   Now when you are done chatting, it is easy to restore
   your comment line to its original value.

1.90 : (Public Release 1/15/98)
 - Added ARexx-script callbacks to all logging events. (i.e., you
   can have your ARexx script run when an event occurs)
 - Added the STARTSCRIPT/K, ENDSCRIPT/K, DEFAULTSCRIPT/K, CONNECTSCRIPT/K,
   LOGONSCRIPT/K, LOGOFFSCRIPT/K, UPDATESCRIPT/K, CONNECTSCRIPT/K,
   and DISCONNECTSCRIPT/K @{"startup arguments" link ToolTypes}.
 - Added support for logging AMarquee System Messages. (and thus 
   requires amarquee.library v46)
 - Added the Scrolling Log View to QAmiTrack.
 - Added the "Log View" submenu and "Clear Log View" menu item
   to the Options menu.
 - Added the LOGVIEWLEVEL/K and LOGVIEWLENGTH/K/N @{"startup arguments" link ToolTypes}.
 - Removed the keyboard shortcuts for the Server, Port, and Comment
   string gadgets.  Now all keystrokes into the QAmiTrack window
   cause the Comment gadget to clear itself and start receiving input.
 - Added callback.rexx to the distribution.
 - Added @{"AREXX" link ARexx} gets and sets for the log view level, log view length,
   and all the callback ARexx script names.
 * Fixed some memory leaks in the ARexx-handling code.
 * Comment changes that don't actually change the comment are no longer
   logged.
 * Removed QAmiTrack's speech output capabilities, since they were
   buggy and little used.  Equivalent functionality can be implemented
   via the ARexx callbacks, if desired.

1.83 : (Public Release 6/20/97)
 - QAmiTrack is now compiled with DICE's automatic stack extention (-gs)
   enabled, so that it shouldn't run out of stack while launching programs
   anymore.

1.82 : (Public Release 6/10/97)
 - If the QAmiTrack hotkey is pressed while the QAmiTrack window
   is already open, the QAmiTrack window will become the active
   window.
 - Added the %U, %C, %R, %T, and %q tokens to the ACTION
   @{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}.
 - Added the SortBy menu, and the SORTBY @{"ToolType" link ToolTypes}.
 * Fixed a bug in the token substitution routine that was causing
   memory corruption when ACTION's were launched.
      
1.81 : (Public Release 6/1/97)
 - Changed the default server to qamitrack.tibb.at, as the old
   QAmiTrack server has gone off-line.
 - Added a Netris entry to the icon's ToolTypes, to support use
   of my other @{"new program" link OtherProgs}.  ;)
   
1.80 : (Public Release 4/9/97)
 - Now uses the asynchronous connect feature of amarquee.library v41,
   so that the GUI no longer freezes while connecting to a server.
 - Now does speech output in a separate thread, so that the QAmiTrack
   GUI does not freeze when the speech synthesizer is speaking.

1.70 : (Public Release 2/18/97)
 - Added the "View By" submenu, and the @{"VIEWBY" link ToolTypes} ToolType.  Now you
   can identify other hosts by their login name or their real name,
   instead of just by their host name.
 - Disabling QAmiTrack now logs you out of the server, instead of
   just making you invisible.
 - A plus symbol is now listed in the third column of entries for
   clients who have their QAmiTrack window open.
 - Added the @{"VISIBLETO" link ToolTypes} ToolType, which allows you to choose which
   other clients can see that you are online.
 - Rewrote the ACTION @{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes} to handle more substitution sequences.
 - Added the VIEWBY, VISIBLETO, USERNAME, USERNAMES, REALNAME, REALNAMES,
   and WINOPEN argument to the "get" ARexx command.
 - Added the VIEWBY argument to the "set" ARexx command.
 * The QAmiTrack window now consistantly re-opens where it was last placed.
   (Before it would only do this if you had resized it after moving it)
 * QAmiTrack no longer brings up "Please insert volume SPEAK:"
   requesters on systems that do not have the SPEAK: device mounted.
 * QAmiTrack is no longer quite as agressive about reconnecting
   after it has been disconnected.  It will now wait for up to one 
   reconnect period before trying again.

1.60 : (Public Release 2/9/97)
 - QAmiTrack is now much more tenacious about getting online and
   staying online.  If it is not connected to the server, it will
   attempt at regular intervals to connect to it, and if a connection
   is broken, it will immediately attempt to reconnect.
 - Added the @{"RECONNECTDELAY" link ToolTypes} ToolType.
 - Added Speech output, and the @{"SPEAKLEVEL" link ToolTypes} ToolType.
 - Added Logging, and the @{"LOGFILE" link ToolTypes} and @{"LOGLEVEL" link ToolTypes} ToolTypes.
 - Added ARexx @{"gets" link ARexx} and @{"sets" link ARexx} for the SPEAKLEVEL, LOGLEVEL, and LOGFILE
   variables.
 - Split the Project menu into the Project and Options Menus.
 - Added the Speech Level and Log Level submenus.
 - Added the ability to use the arrow keys to "scroll" the currently
   selected ListView item.
 - Increased the maximum comment length from 64 chars to 1023.
 * QAmiTrack no longer puts up an error requester when it is
   launched while already running.
 * The Comment string gadget now updates properly when the "set comment"
   ARexx command is received.
 * Fixed a potential memory leak.
  
1.50 : (Public Release 2/5/97)
 - Converted AmiTrack into QAmiTrack, which uses @{"amarquee.library" link amarquee.library}
   and AMarqueed instead of a custom server.  First release of
   this version!

@endnode

@node Requirements

To use QAmiTrack, you will need the following:

 - An Amiga with some free memory
 - Workbench 2.04 or greater
 - An Internet connection
 - AmiTCP (or a compatible TCP stack, or Inet225) set up and running.
 - @{"amarquee.library" link amarquee.library} v46+ in your LIBS: directory.
 
@endnode

@node Acks

Thanks to Thomas Steinbichler for providing the AMarquee server
that QAmiTrack runs on (qamitrack.tibb.at)

Thanks to Michael Balzer for ARexxBox, upon which all of 
QAmiTrack's ARexx support is based.

Thanks to Paul Gooch for testing and bug-reports.

Thanks to Oliver Hotz for providing the previous server for so long...

Thanks to Fredrik Rambris for the nice "footprint" icons!

@endnode


@node Introduction

What is QAmiTrack?  Hmm, good question.

I was talking to an AmiPhone user a while ago, and
he was lamenting that it was hard to find another AmiPhone
user who was online to talk to.  We decided what was needed
was a way to find out who else is on line, sort of an
"Active Amiga registry".

So that's what QAmiTrack does.  QAmiTrack is an AMarquee program
that allows you to see what other Amigas are online at the moment.  
It isn't limited to just AmiPhone users, either; you can register 
your Amiga to advertise any message string you want.

Note that QAmiTrack requires @{"amarquee.library" link amarquee.library} v46+ to be 
installed in your LIBS: directory.

The following files should be in the QAmiTrack archive:

