@node Installation

Just copy the executable file and icon to wherever you want 
to keep them.  If you can spare the RAM, I recommend placing
them in your sys:WBStartup directory, so that it will be launched 
whenever you boot.  It will automatically log in whenever you start up
your TCP software.  Make sure that @{"amarquee.library" link amarquee.library} is installed
in your LIBS: directory!

If you wish to use the ACTION (app-launching) feature of QAmiTrack,
it is very likely you will have to modify the paths in the ACTION
ToolTypes to suit the paths in your system.

@endnode

@node ClientArgs

ARexx scripts launched by QAmiTrack via the *SCRIPT/K keywords
are passed arguments containing information about the event that
caused the script to be launched.  These arguments are passed
in a standardized format, with between one and six arguments,
all separated by '^' characters.  This is to make it easy to
parse arguments even though they may have spaces in them (although
it admittedly causes some trouble if the arguments have '^'
characters in them!)

To parse out the arguments given by QAmiTrack to your ARexx script,
use a command like this:

/* An arexx script that will be launched by QAmiTrack... */
parse arg arg1 "^" arg2 "^" arg3 "^" arg4 "^" arg5 "^" arg6

/* ... */

For all scripts, the first argument will be a keyword indicating
the ToolType that caused the launch.  E.g. if the script was
launched due to a connect event, arg1 above would be set to
'CONNECTSCRIPT'.  Or, if the script launch was due to someone 
updating their entry, arg1 would be set to 'UPDATESCRIPT'.
This argument is useful if you are using the DEFAULTSCRIPT/K
argument to allow one ARexx script to handle all event types,
or if you set multiple *SCRIPT/K arguments to launch the same
script.

The other arguments will vary based on what type of event
caused the ARexx script launch.  To wit:

if arg1 is UPDATESCRIPT, LOGONSCRIPT, or LOGOFFSCRIPT, then
  arg2 = IP name of the client that caused the event.
  arg3 = username of the client that caused the event.
  arg4 = realname of the client that caused the event.
  arg5 = 'Y' if the client who caused the event has his
         QAmitrack window open, else 'N' if it is iconified.
  arg6 = The comment line of the client that caused the event.

if arg1 is CONNECTSCRIPT or DISCONNECTSCRIPT, then
  arg2 = The name of the current AMarquee server, as shown
         in the "Server" string gadget of the QAmiTrack GUI.
         
if arg1 is STARTSCRIPT or ENDSCRIPT, then no other arguments are passed.

if arg1 is SYSMESSAGESCRIPT, then
  arg2 = The IP name of the computer from which the system
         message originated.
  arg3 = The text contents of the system message.

@endnode

@node ToolTypes

QAmiTrack understands the following parameters.  These parameters
may be set either as ToolTypes in QAmiTrack's icon, or specified
on the command line (in the same exact format as the tooltypes,
although you may have to use "quote marks" if the parameter 
contains spaces):

SERVER/K: 
    The Internet host name of the Amiga that is running the AMarquee
    server that you wish to register with.  This defaults to qamitrack.tibb.at.

PORT/K/N: 
    The port number on the server which you wish to connect to.
    This defaults to port 2957 (the standard AMarqueed port).

COMMENT/K: 
    The comment string you wish to have associated with your Amiga.
    This defaults to "" (i.e. no comment).

ENABLED/K:
    If set to NO, QAmiTrack will open in "disabled" mode.  In this
    mode, QAmiTrack will not connect to the server.

RAGGEDTEXT/K:
    If set to YES, QAmitrack will display items in "ragged text"
    mode, with the comment for each line displayed one column after
    the hostname.  If set to NO (the default), all the comments
    will be aligned on a column determined by the longest hostname.

BEEPONLOG/K:
    If set to YES, QAmitrack will do a DisplayBeep (e.g. screen flash)
    any time an entry is written to the Log View.  Handy for when
    you don't want to miss someone coming or going, but don't want
    to watch the QAmiTrack window like a hawk...
    
CONFIRMAPPLAUNCH/K:
    If set to NO, QAmiTrack will not double-check with you whether
    or not you really wanted to launch an app when you double
    clicked on an entry in the ListView.  Has no effect unless
    at least one ACTION parameter was also specified.
    
ALLOWMULTIPLE/K:
    If set to YES, QAmiTrack will allow you to run more than one
    copy of it at once.  In this way, you can be connected to
    more than one server at a time, if necessary.  (Note:  You
    still won't be able to have more than 1 entry on at any given 
    AMarquee server!)
    
CX_POPUP/K:
    If set to NO, QAmiTrack will not open its window on startup.

CX_PRIORITY/K/N:
    Sets the Commodities priority of the QAmiTrack commodity.
    Defaults to zero.
    
CX_POPKEY/K:
    Sets a hotkey that will cause QAmiTrack to open its window.
    Defaults to "lcommand shift a".

RECONNECTDELAY/K/N:
    Specifies, in minutes, the delay period between successive
    attempts to connect to the server.  If set to a negative
    value, no such attempts will be made.  The default value
    is two minutes.

LOGFILE/K:
    Specifies the pathname and filename that log events should
    be appended to.  (The default is "", meaning no log output)
    
LOGLEVEL/K:
    Specifies how much logging should take place, both to a file
    (if one was specified with the LOGFILE argument) and to the 
    Log View.  This ToolType may be set to one of four levels:  
    NONE, TERSE, MODERATE (the default), or VERBOSE.  With NONE 
    selected, no output will be written to the log file, and only 
    system messages will be output to the Log View.  TERSE output 
    will only log an entry when the connection to the server has 
    been closed, or when a client logs onto or off of the server.  
    With MODERATE selected, a log entry will also be made when a 
    connection to the server is established, and when someone 
    changes their comment string.  With VERBOSE selected, log 
    entries will be made when QAmiTrack starts up or quits, as well.

LOGVIEWLEVEL/K:
    Specifies how much of the QAmiTrack GUI space should be used
    by the scrolling Log View.  This keyword lets you set the
    initial setting of the "Log View" submenu of the Options
    menu.  Values that may be passed with this argument are:
    OFF, 25%, 50%, 75%, or 100%.  (The default for this argument
    is 25%)
    
LOGVIEWLENGTH/K/N:
    Specifies how many lines of the log should be kept in the
    Log View.  Note that this only affects the GUI; it does
    not affect any output being sent to a file. (The default 
    for this argument is 50)

ACTION0/K, ACTION1/K, ..., ACTION19/K:
    These 20 different ToolTypes can be used to allow QAmiTrack
    to launch other programs by double-clicking on an item in
    the ListView.  The values for these parameters must be in
    the form Label,Action.  The label will be displayed in the 
    cycle gadget at the right, and when an entry in the list is 
    double-clicked, its associated Action string will be run
    as if it had been typed into a shell.  Also, the following
    tokens may be included in the value string:
    
      %h - Hostname of the target client.
      %s - Hostname of the target client (for backwards compatibility).

      %u - Username of the target client.
      %U - Your username.

      %c - Comment line of the target client.
      %C - Your comment line.

      %r - Real name of the user at the target client.
      %R - Your real name.

      %l - Entire ListView entry of the target client.

      %t - Number of minutes since the target client was updated.
      %T - Number of minutes since your client was updated.

      %% - One percent symbol.
      %q - One quote mark (")

    When the command is run, these token will be replaced with their
    values, as listed above.
    
    Note that any application you run this way will by default
    have both stdin and stdout directed to NIL:.  If you want
    to be able to access either or both of these streams, you
    will need to specify a redirect ('>' or '<') in your action
    string.
    
TOP/K/N, LEFT/K/N, WIDTH/K/N, HEIGHT/K/N:
    These ToolTypes can be used to customize the default placement
    of the QAmiTrack window on-screen.

VISIBLETO/K:
    This ToolType allows you to specify, via a regular expression,
    which other QAmiTrack clients you wish to be visible to.  By 
    default, it is set to #?, meaning everybody.  But if you wished, 
    for example, to only be seen by educational sites, you could set 
    it to #?.edu.  Or, if you only wish to rendezvous with one Amiga,
    just set it to that Amiga's hostname.    

VIEWBY/K:
    This ToolType determines how other clients should be identified
    on screen and in the logs.  It can be set to "hostname", "username", 
    or "realname", and this choice will be reflected in the "view by" 
    submenu of the Options menu.  The default for this parameter is 
    to show the hostname.

SORTBY/K:
    This ToolType determines how the on-screen listings should be
    sorted.  It can be set to "age", "name", "comment", or "none".
    This choice will be reflected in thee "view by" submenu of the
    Options menu.  The default for this parameter is to sort by age.
        
USERNAME/K:
    This ToolType allows you to override your login name with whatever
    login you wish to present to the world. (up to 8 characters long).
    If this ToolType is not specified, QAmiTrack will try to get the
    login name from the ENV variables USERNAME, USER, or LOGNAME.
    
REALNAME/K:
    This ToolType allows you to override your real name with whatever
    name you wish.  If this ToolType is not specified, QAmiTrack will
    look in the ENV variable REALNAME to try and find it.
    
LOGONSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever somebody logs on to the AMarquee server with
    QAmiTrack (i.e. whenever a new entry appears in the ListView).
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.
    
LOGOFFSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever somebody logs off of the AMarquee server with
    QAmiTrack (i.e. whenever an entry disappears from the ListView).
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

UPDATESCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever somebody changes their entry on the AMarquee 
    server with QAmiTrack.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

CONNECTSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever the QAmiTrack client connects to an AMarquee
    server.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

DISCONNECTSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever the QAmiTrack disconnects from (or is 
    disconnected from) an AMarquee server.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

STARTSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed when QAmiTrack is launched.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

ENDSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed when QAmiTrack quits.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

DEFAULTSCRIPT/K:
    Lets you specify the filename of an ARexx script that will be 
    executed whenever ANY of the above events happens.  Specifying
    any of the above *SCRIPT/K arguments will override that argument
    for that event type only.
    Arguments to the script look like @{"this" link ClientArgs}.

Some valid QAmiTrack CLI invocations would be:

  QAmiTrack

  QAmiTrack "COMMENT=I'm online!" LEFT=50 TOP=10 VISIBLETO=~(#?.au) LOGVIEWLEVEL=75%

  QAmiTrack SERVER=your.mother.com PORT=5217 CX_POPUP=NO "COMMENT=My comment"

  QAmiTrack "COMMENT=Hi there" "CX_POPKEY=shift help" ENABLED=NO RECONNECTDELAY=1

  QAmiTrack "ACTION0=AmiPhone,AmiTCP:bin/AmiPhone CONNECT=%s" "ACTION1=finger,finger @%s >CON://///WAIT/CLOSE"
  
  QAmiTrack "ACTION0=FTP,AmiTCP:bin/ncFTP %s <>CON:" RAGGEDTEXT=YES

  QAmiTrack "COMMENT=I'm wired" DEFAULTSCRIPT=work:Rexx/myRexxScript.rexx
 
@endnode

@node Using
 
QAmiTrack's GUI is fairly straightforward.  It consists of several
string gadgets and two ListViews.  The Server, Port, and Comment string 
gadgets show which AMarquee server and port you are connected to,
and the comment line that you are displaying to other QAmiTrack users,
respectively.  The first ListView shows the identifier strings and comment 
strings  of everyone logged in to the server you are connected to.  
Each ListView entry will also show, on the left, the number of minutes 
that have elapsed since the entry was last changed.  This field will be 
blank if more than 99 minutes have elapsed since the last update of that 
entry.  If that client's QAmiTrack window is currently open, a plus symbol 
('+') will appear between the elapsed time counter and the identifier string.
The identifier string may be either the computer's hostname, the user's
login name, or the user's real name, depending on the current setting
of the "View By" menu.

If any of the ACTION startup arguments were specified, a cycle gadget
will also be present at the right side of the window.  The cycle
gadget indicates the name of the currently selected action.  
Double-clicking in the ListView will execute the command associated
with the current state of the cycle gadget.  See ACTION0...ACTION19/K
in the @{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes} section for how to customize the cycle gadget.

Also, once you have single-clicked on an enty in the ListView, 
you can "scroll" its comment line left and right with the arrow 
keys on the keyboard.  This can be useful for reading long comment
lines when the QAmiTrack window is narrow.

The second, lower, ListView is the Log View.  This ListView displays
records of events that have occurred recently, such as people
logging on or off, or people's comments.  The "Log View" submenu
of the Options menu can be used to specify how much window space
ListView takes up.  The "Log Level" submenu can be used to specify
which events are logged.

QAmiTrack can be hidden by clicking its close box, or via the 
Project menu.  Its window can be reopened via its hotkey 
(see the CX_POPKEY @{"ToolType" link ToolTypes}) or by clicking the "Show" button in the 
Commodities Exchange program.

The "Enabled" option in the Options menu controls whether or
not you wish to be connected to (and hence, included in) the 
AMarquee server's Amiga registry.  That is to say, if you
disable QAmiTrack, it will disconnect from the server, rendering
you "invisible" to other QAmiTrack users.  You can also use the 
Enable/Disable buttons in the Commodities Exchange program is to 
control this.

The "Confirm" option in the Options menu, if checked, will
cause QAmiTrack to bring up a requester when you double click
a ListView entry, making sure that you really wanted to launch 
a program.

The "Ragged Text" item, in the Options menu, controls how the text 
in the ListView is to be formatted.  If this option is checked, 
the comment string for each line will appear directly after the 
hostname.  Left unchecked, this option will cause the comment strings 
to be aligned in a single column.

The "Beep On Log" item, in the Options menu, determines whether
or not QAmiTrack should flash the screen (via DisplayBeep())
whenever it logs an event to the Log View.

The "Log Level" submenu in the Options menu is used to control how 
much output QAmiTrack will generate when an event occurs.  The submenu 
has four items: "None", "Terse", "Moderate", and "Verbose", which
behave as follows:

  In "None" mode, no events are logged to the log file or 
  the Log View.
  
  In "Terse" mode, QAmiTrack will only write to the log file when 
  the server connection is closed, or when a client entry appears 
  or disappears from the ListView.  The Log View will only record 
  comment update events.

  In "Moderate" mode, a client changing his/her comment line will 
  also be noted in the log file, and clients logging in and out 
  will be noted in the Log View.  

  In "Verbose" mode, all events are noted in both the log file and 
  the Log View.

The "Sort By" submenu allows you to choose how the QAmiTrack client
listings will be ordered in the ListView.  If set to "Age", then the 
listings will be sorted based on how long it's been since they were 
updated--the most recently changed listings will be listed first.  
"Name" will sort based on the displayed name for the listing (which 
will be the user's login name, hostname, or real name, based on the 
View By parameter).  "Comment" will sort based on the user's comment 
string, and "none" will leave the list unsorted.

The "View By" submenu allows you to choose how the various
QAmiTrack clients are to be listed in the ListView.  It has three
options, "Host Name", "User Name", and "Real Name".  If the first of
these is checked, clients will be listed by IP name (e.g. sdcc8.ucsd.edu).
If "User Name" is checked, then the person's login name will be used
(e.g. jfriesne).  Or, if "Real Name" is checked, the person's real
name will be used (e.g. Jeremy Friesner).

The "Revert Comment" menu item will restore your comment line
to the value it had when QAmiTrack was launched (e.g., the
value specified in the COMMENT ToolType)

The "Clear Log View" will (you guessed it) clear the Log View display.

Keystrokes typed into the QAmiTrack window will be directed
to the "Comment" string gadget, to allow for easy on-line chatting.

@endnode

@node ARexx

The QAmiTrack client features an ARexx interface.  Scripts
from the included "ARexx" directory may be used with this 
interface, or you can write your own.  ARexx Commands understood
by QAmiTrack are listed here:

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Command:     CONNECT
 
Description: Causes QAmiTrack to launch an application, similar to
             to double-clicking on an entry in the ListView.

Arguments:   ACTION/K - Name of the app to launch (as it appears in
                        the cycle gadget)
             ACTIONINDEX/K/N - Index number of the app to launch
             HOST/K - Name of the host to connect to, as it appears
                      in the ListView.
             HOSTINDEX/K/S - Index of the host in the list to connect to.
             CONFIRM/K - Boolean override for the "Confirm Launch"
                         menu option.

Results:     0 if the app was launched, 5 if there were problems with
             the arguments specified, 10 if the app launch failed.

Notes:       All arguments are optional.  If not otherwise specified,
             the currently specified action will be launched on the
             the previouly clicked host.

Example:     CONNECT ACTION 'AmiPhone' HOSTINDEX 2 CONFIRM false

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Command:     GET

Description: Returns various state information.  All values except the
             string-array (/M) values are returned automatically.
             To also return the string-arrays, specify their corresponding
             switch argument (CLIENTS/S or ACTIONS/S).

Arguments:   CLIENTS/S - return the lists of clients and their comment strings.
             ACTIONS/S - return the lists of GUI user-actions and their shell commands.

Results:     SERVER - IP name the QAmiTrackServer is currently connected to.
             PORT/N - port number the QAmiTrackServer connected to.
             CONFIRM/N - 1 iff "Confirm" in the Project menu is checked.
             CONNECTED/N - 1 iff QAmiTrack has a valid connection to a server.
             NUMCLIENTS/N - The number of QAmiTrack clients in the client list.
             ENABLED/N - 1 iff "Enabled" in the Project menu is checked.
             NUMACTIONS/N - The number of actions available in the cycle gadget.
             HIDDEN/N - 1 iff the window is hidden (i.e. not open).
             COMMENT - The current comment string for this QAmiTrack client.
             LASTENTRYCLICKED/N - Index of the last client entry clicked on by the user.
             MYHOSTNAME - What QAmiTrack thinks the local IP name is.
             LOGLEVEL - The current logging level, as a string (e.g. "verbose")
             LOGFILE - The filename of the log file being output to.
             VISIBLETO - The regular expression governing which other clients can see us.
             VIEWBY - The current viewing mode ("hostname", "username", or "realname").
             CURRENTACTION/N - Index of the currently selected user action.
             ACTIONS/M - Array [0..NUMACTIONS-1] of user actions in cycle gadget.  ACTIONS/S must have been specified.
             COMMANDS/M - Array [0..NUMACTIONS-1] of corresponding shell commands.  ACTIONS/S must have been specified.
             CLIENTS/M - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of current QAmiTrack client hostnames.
             REALNAMES/M - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of current QAmiTrack Real Names.
             USERNAMES/M - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of current QAmiTrack User Names.
             WINOPEN/M/N - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of booleans:  1 iff that client's window is open
             LASTCHANGED/M/N - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of time elapsed since client last changed (in minutes).
             COMMENTS/M - Array [0..NUMCLIENTS-1] of comments associated with the clients.
             LOGVIEWLENGTH/N - Maximum number of lines visible in the Scrolling Log View.
             LOGVIEWLEVEL/N - Current % of the view space used by the Scrolling Log View (0 - 100)
             LOGONSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when a client logs on (or "" if unset)
             LOGOFFSCRIPT -Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when a client logs off (or "" if unset)
             UPDATESCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when a client changes his comment (or "" if unset)
             CONNECTSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack connects to a server (or "" if unset)
             DISCONNECTSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack disconnects from a server (or "" if unset)
             ENDSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack quits (or "" if unset)
             STARTSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that is launched when QAmiTrack starts (or "" if unset)
             DEFAULTSCRIPT - Name of the ARexx script that will be launched when an event occurs that has no
                             ARexx script assigned to specifically to it (or "" if no default is set)
             BEEPONLOG/K - Boolean describing the state of the "Beep On Log" feature.
             
Notes:       The numeric return value -1 means "invalid".

Example:     See ARexx/TestTrackRexx.rexx

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Command:     QUIT

Description: Causes QAmiTrack to exit.

Arguments:   None.

Results:     None.

Notes:       

Example:     QUIT

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Command:     REQUEST

Description: Causes QAmiTrack to display an EasyRequester to the user

Arguments:   TITLE/K - Text to be put in the requester's title
             MESSAGE/K - Text to be put in the requester's main body
             BUTTONS/K - '|' separated list of button labels.
             
Results:     CLICKED/N - Index of which button the user clicked.
                         The right-hand button is index 0, and
                         the left hand button is index 1.  For Each
                         successive button after the lefthand button,
                         the index is incremented by 1.

Notes:       (Semi)appropriate default strings are used for any keywords
             not specified.

Example:     options results
             request stem rq. TITLE '"'||"My Title"||'"' MESSAGE '"'||"My Message"||'"' BUTTONS "Yes|Maybe|No"
             if (rq.clicked == 0) then say "you said no!"
             if (rq.clicked == 1) then say "you said yes!"
             if (rq.clicked == 2) then say "you said maybe!"             

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Command:     SET

Description: Changes any of a number of settings in QAmiTrack.  

Arguments:   ENABLED/K - Boolean to enable/disable QAmiTrack.
             HIDDEN/K - Boolean to show/hide the QAmiTrack window.
             CONFIRM/K - Boolean to enable/disable app launch confirmation requesters.
             LEFT/K/N - Sets the left edge position of the QAmiTrack window (in pixels).
             TOP/K/N - Sets the top edge position of the QAmiTrack window (in pixels).
             WIDTH/K/N - Sets the width of the QAmiTrack window (in pixels).
             HEIGHT/K/N - Sets the height of the QAmiTrack window (in pixels).
             COMMENT/K - Sets the current comment in the QAmiTrack window.
             SERVER/K - Sets (and attempts to connect to) a new server.
             WINDOWTITLE - Displays a message in the QAmiTrack Window's title bar.
             CURRENTACTION/K - Selects a new current user action (by label).
             CURRENTACTIONINDEX/K/N - Selects a new current user action (by index, first entry = 0).
             LOGLEVEL/K - Sets the current logging level, as a string (e.g. "verbose")
             LOGFILE/K - Sets the log file being output to (specify as a path & filename).
             ACTION/K - Adds/Changes/Deletes a user action (see Notes, below).
             VIEWBY/K - Sets the current view mode (to "hostname", "username", or "realname").
             LOGVIEWLENGTH/N - Sets the Maximum number of lines visible in the Scrolling Log View.
             LOGVIEWLEVEL/N - Sets the % of the view space used by the Scrolling Log View (0 - 100, in increments of 25)
             LOGONSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when clients log on.
             LOGOFFSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when clientn log off.
             UPDATESCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when clients change their comment.
             CONNECTSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack connects to a server.
             DISCONNECTSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack disconnects from a server.
             ENDSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when QAmiTrack quits.
             STARTSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that is launched when QAmiTrack starts (this is probably not useful!)
             DEFAULTSCRIPT/K - Sets the name of the ARexx script that will be launched when an event occurs that has no
                                ARexx script assigned to specifically to it.
             BEEPONLOG/K - Boolean to turn on/off the "Beep On Log" feature.
             
Results:     ACTIONINDEX/N - If the ACTION keyword was used, this result will
                             contain the index of the affected user action.

Notes:       Boolean arguments may be set using YES, NO, 1, 0, TRUE, or FALSE.

             Window dimensions will be truncated to the nearest legal setting.
             This allows one to make the window as small as possible by specifying
             WIDTH 0 HEIGHT 0, for example.
             
             The ACTION keyword takes a string of the form "Name,Action".
             If a user action with the name Name already exists, it will
             be modified to use the new Action string.  If not, such
             a user action will be added to the end of the list.  If
             you specify a Name without an Action, that User action will
             be deleted from the cycle gadget.
             
Example:     options results
             SET LEFT 15 HEIGHT 300 ENABLED true HIDDEN false SERVER localhost
             SET LOGVIEWLEVEL 50 DEFAULTSCRIPT "ram:callback.rexx"
             SET VIEWBY realname LOGLEVEL verbose 
             SET ACTION '"'||"AmiPhone,work:AmiPhone/AmiPhone %s"||'"'
             SET ACTION stem res. "TestAction,c:testProgram"
             say "TestAction's index is " res.actionindex
             SET CURRENTACTIONINDEX res.actionindex  /* One way to do it... */
             SET CURRENTACTION "TestAction"          /* And the other way... */
             SET ACTION "AmiPhone"  /* Delete the AmiPhone user action */
@endnode             

